<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">BARCLAYS EARNINGS DISAPPOINT <span class="divider">Â |Â </span></span><!-- end .title --> Barclays said on Tuesday that its first-quarter profit declined 5 percent as revenue from trading bonds, currencies and commodities fell, <b><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/05/06/barclays-earnings-slip-5-on-challenging-fixed-income-environment">DealBookâs Chad Bray reports</a></b>. Barclays reported an <b>adjusted first-quarter pretax profit of 1.69 billion pounds</b>, or about $2.85 billion, compared with profit of Â£1.79 billion in the period a year earlier. Analysts had expected the bank to post an adjusted pretax profit of Â£1.82 billion.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Barclays is in the midst of overhauling its operations</b> as it aims to reshape itself into a smaller investment bank focused on higher-return and less-risky businesses. On Monday, the bank confirmed that its global head of mergers, Paul G. Parker, <b><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/05/05/barclays-confirms-its-head-of-mergers-is-leaving">was leaving</a></b> â the latest prominent departure from the bank.</p>
